{"questionId":"2672705","questionHtml":"<p>Hence or otherwise, write an expression for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>u</mi><mi>n</mi></msub></math> in terms of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>n</mi></math>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><strong>EITHER</strong></p>\n<p>valid attempt to find <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>d</mi></math> (may be seen in (a) or (b))&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong> </em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>d</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>OR</strong></p>\n<p>valid attempt to find <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>S</mi><mi>n</mi></msub><mo>-</mo><msub><mi>S</mi><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong> </em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>n</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>4</mn><mi>n</mi><mo>-</mo><mo>(</mo><msup><mi>n</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>n</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>4</mn><mi>n</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>)</mo></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>OR</strong></p>\n<p>equating <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>n</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>4</mn><mi>n</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>n</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>(</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>+</mo><msub><mi>u</mi><mi>n</mi></msub><mo>)</mo></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong> </em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mi>n</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>8</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>+</mo><msub><mi>u</mi><mi>n</mi></msub></math> (or equivalent)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong><em>(A1)</em></strong></p>\n<p><strong>THEN</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>u</mi><mi>n</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>(</mo><mi>n</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>)</mo></math> OR <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>u</mi><mi>n</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>n</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>3</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em><br><br><br></p>\n<p><em><strong>[3 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"2672705","referenceCode":"23M.1.SL.TZ1.8c","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Hence or otherwise, write an expression for un in terms of n.","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"c","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 3]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 1—Number and algebra","Topic 1—Number and algebra","SL 1.2—Arithmetic sequences and series"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}